**Quick Reference --- Running Bandit**

+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| **Running Bandit against          | **Interpreting the Output**       |
| vulnerable_shop.py**              |                                   |
+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| \# Install                        | -   **Severity:** HIGH / MEDIUM / |
|                                   |     LOW --- how dangerous if      |
| pip3 install bandit               |     exploited                     |
| \--break-system-packages          |                                   |
|                                   | -   **Confidence:** HIGH / MEDIUM |
| \# Run against a single file      |     / LOW --- how sure Bandit is  |
|                                   |     the finding is real (not a    |
| bandit vulnerable_shop.py         |     false positive)               |
|                                   |                                   |
| \# Run with lower noise (medium+  | -   **-ll flag:** suppress LOW    |
| severity only)                    |     severity findings --- useful  |
|                                   |     for reducing noise in large   |
| bandit -ll vulnerable_shop.py     |     codebases                     |
|                                   |                                   |
| \# Run recursively over a         | -   **Test IDs:** B-prefixed      |
| directory                         |     codes (B105, B201\...) are    |
|                                   |     stable --- safe to use in CI  |
| bandit -r ./module4_owasp_bingo/  |     allowlists and exception      |
|                                   |     files                         |
| \# Output as JSON for CI pipeline |                                   |
| integration                       | -   **False positives:** Bandit   |
|                                   |     reports B324 (MD5) even when  |
| bandit -f json -o                 |     used for checksums, not       |
| bandit_report.json                |     passwords. Always review      |
| vulnerable_shop.py                |     context before filing as      |
|                                   |     false positive                |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | -   **Exit codes:** exit 0 = no   |
|                                   |     issues found, exit 1 = issues |
|                                   |     found. CI pipelines can gate  |
|                                   |     on exit code to block PRs     |
|                                   |     with HIGH findings            |
+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **pip-audit --- Checking Dependencies for Known CVEs**                |
|                                                                       |
| **Bandit analyses your own code.** pip-audit analyses your            |
| dependencies. Both tools together cover the two main attack surfaces  |
| in the OWASP A03 Software Supply Chain category: vulnerabilities you  |
| wrote, and vulnerabilities you inherited.                             |
|                                                                       |
| Install and run against the Module 5 demo file:                       |
|                                                                       |
| > pip3 install pip-audit \--break-system-packages                     |
| >                                                                     |
| > pip-audit -r requirements_vulnerable.txt                            |
|                                                                       |
| **Expected output:** pip-audit will list CVE IDs, affected package    |
| versions, severity scores, and fixed versions for each vulnerable     |
| dependency. Flask 1.0.0 alone carries multiple HIGH-severity CVEs.    |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
